The paper deals with estimating geometric distortion in video feeds, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of motion features and surveillance systems suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which could place it under the machine learning (cs.MM), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
